  "body": "I have created a deployment script which deploys 18 contracts.\r\nThe script runs fine on the hardhat network, but when the forking option is activated, it fails with the following error: \r\n\r\n`Error: Transaction failed: revert\r\n    at new TransactionExecutionError (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/errors.ts:97:16)\r\n    at HardhatNode._manageErrors (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:969:12)\r\n    at HardhatNode.estimateGas (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:508:27)\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at EthModule._estimateGasAction (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:390:9)\r\n    at HardhatNetworkProvider.request (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:102:18)\r\n    at EthersProviderWrapper.send (/project/node_modules/hardhat-deploy-ethers/src/ethers-provider-wrapper.ts:13:20)`\r\n\r\n`Caused by: Error: Transaction failed: revert\r\n    at new TransactionExecutionError (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/errors.ts:97:16)\r\n    at HardhatNode._manageErrors (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:969:12)\r\n    at HardhatNode.estimateGas (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:508:27)\r\n    at runMicrotasks (<anonymous>)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at EthModule._estimateGasAction (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:390:9)\r\n    at HardhatNetworkProvider.request (/project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:102:18)\r\n    at EthersProviderWrapper.send (/project/node_modules/hardhat-deploy-ethers/src/ethers-provider-wrapper.ts:13:20)`\r\n\r\nWhen commenting out deployed contracts code, I have noticed that whenever I am deploying 12 contracts in total or less (doesn't matter which ones), the scripts runs without error.\r\nIs there a limitation to the amount of contracts to be deployed ?\r\nIt seems to be a gas estimation issue, but I've passed the following gas options : \r\n`blockGasLimit: 0x1fffffffffffff,\r\n  allowUnlimitedContractSize: true`\r\n\r\nWhich should prevent any gas problems.",
