    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This strange bound on the number of allowed contract deployments hints at some kind of nonce error.  If you look at the deployer address on the network you are forking, is the 13th outgoing transaction a contract creation?  If so, then doing a forked net deploy where the 13th transaction is a contract creation will fail due to Hardhat's current behavior of resetting an unlocked address' nonce to 0.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/issues/1231",
